			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When Creating Remember:
<br />

<br />
<B><I>
<br />
This is mearly a guide to give you ideas on what race to be and what stats to choose...
<br />

<br />
Chose a race/class combo you like.
<br />

<br />
You should choose your own stats, but if you have a hard time here are suggestions...
<br />
</B></I>
<br />

<br />
<B>Notes on stats:</b>
<br />

<br />
<B>Strength</b> determines your maximum carrying capacity without slowing down
<br />

<br />
<b>Stamina</b> is used in determining hp-per-level, 100+ Stamina will also make it so you do not suffer from "fatigue"(no yellow bar).. except by the fact you can't jump.
<br />

<br />
<b>Agility</b> is used soley in DEFENSIVE skill raising, it has a -very- minor role in AC, just be sure to keep AGI over 75 at all tiems(even after you're playing)
<br />

<br />
<b>Dexterity</b> increases 'proc' chances on weapons as well as chance to increase an offensive skill
<br />

<br />
<b>Wisdom</b> is used to determine your maximum Mana(as a wis caster), and also used in trade skills if higer then INT
<br />

<br />
<b>Intelligence</b> is used to determine a pure-casters max mana(enc/wiz/mag/nec), and also sed in trade skills if higer then WIS
<br />

<br />
<b>Charisma</b> effects the buy/sell rates with NPC's, once you have 105 chr, no more chr will help prices
<br />

<br />
<B>Notes on Melee &amp; Priest:</b> In the tables below you will see "Melee" and "Priest" colums, which is basicly designed to more specifically let you know where to put your points based on what you want to do... (Melee next to your pet--or sit back and cast/heal)... If you want to do a bit of both, mix and match...
<br />

<br />
REMEMBER!: Be sure to keep Stamina, Agility, Dexterity, and Wisdom over 75 at all times! It's commonly called a "magic number" for stats, meaning if you have 75 OR higher in those stats, You'll get a HUGE boost compared to any other stat point gains... (Some people report to loose 50-100AC when they go under 75 AGI at high-40's+, but at -no- other number is these changes so noticeable)
<br />

<br />
Barbarian Beastlords have the best rounded-out stats for melee &amp; priest combo... In My opinion =p</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
